initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.

The World Dance Competition is right on the horizon and this year, it's being held in Tokyo, Japan.

Get all the latest details on the event right here.

Representing the USA in 2024 is Mia Rodriguez, who will be showcasing her routine, "Rhythm of the Heart".

But what is going through her mind as she prepares for the stage, where she'll dance in front of a live audience of thousands!

I had the chance to catch up with her to get the inside scoop on how she's gearing up for the competition.

The World Dance Competition Grand Final will be broadcasted on NBC and Peacock on Saturday, June 15.

The stage was set, the lights dimmed, and the excitement palpable as Mia Rodriguez stood backstage, ready to showcase her routine, "Rhythm of the Heart" to the world. The World Dance Competition in Tokyo, Japan was the biggest event of her career, and she couldn't help but feel a mix of nerves and excitement coursing through her veins.

As she closed her eyes, taking deep breaths to calm her racing heart, she reminded herself of all the hours of practice, sweat, and determination that had led her to this moment. The cheers of the crowd filtered through the curtains, and Mia knew that she was ready.

Stepping onto the stage, the spotlight shining down on her, Mia felt a surge of energy and passion as she began to move to the music. Every step, every turn, every leap was a testament to her dedication and love for dance.

As the music reached its crescendo, Mia's heart beat in time with the rhythm, and she let go of all her fears and insecurities, losing herself in the music and the dance. The crowd roared in approval, and Mia knew that she had given her all on that stage.

As she took her final bow, tears of joy and relief filled her eyes. The World Dance Competition may be over, but Mia Rodriguez knew that this was just the beginning of a bright and promising career in dance.
